# docs/ — where things live

A map of where each kind of document belongs, so `docs/` stays tidy from day one and a new file has an obvious home. **This is the human-readable index; the rule the agent follows is "Where new docs go" in `AGENTS.md`** (modular projects: `.claude/rules/session-discipline.md`). Subfolders are created lazily — a folder appears the first time a file of its type is written, not before. Don't grow the root pile.

## Root (anchors — frequently linked, kept shallow)

| File | What it is |
|---|---|
| `PRD.md` | Product requirements. |
| `ARCHITECTURE.md` | Data model, structure, mental model. |
| `DECISIONS.md` | Full decision log. |
<!-- OPTIONAL: decisions_active_row — include if include_decisions_active == true -->
| `DECISIONS_ACTIVE.md` | Curated index of currently-binding decisions. |

## Subfolders (route new docs here by name)

| Type | Folder |
|---|---|
| `*-brief.md` | `briefs/` |
| `*-handoff.md` | `handoffs/` |
| `*-reference.md`, domain notes | `reference/` |
| research output | `research/` |
| dated session retros | `retros/` |
| audits | `audits/` |
<!-- OPTIONAL: council_map_row — include if "llm-council" in artifact_skills_list -->
| `llm-council` output | `council/` |
<!-- OPTIONAL: brainstorms_map_row — include if "brainstorms" in artifact_skills_list -->
| `brainstorm` output | `brainstorms/` |

Anything not listed routes to a typed subfolder by name. When writing inside a subfolder, use relative links at the correct depth (`../DECISIONS.md`) and confirm cross-references resolve.
